added.title: Lication
added.description: Robin introduces the other Titans to a money making application but they soon learn the dangers of a shareconomy.

added.title: Labor Day
added.description: It's Labor Day and Robin teaches the other Titans about the importance of labor.

added.title: Ones and Zeros
added.description: The Titans build an AI robot so it will create a pizza that's never been made before.

added.title: Career Day
added.description: Robin forces the other Titans to forget their dreams and find regular, boring jobs.

added.title: Classic Titans
added.description: To prove his point about classic superhero cartoons, Control Freak sends the Titans to a former version of Teen Titans Go!

added.title: Everyday Bears
added.description: It's a normal day for the Bears. This means that Ice gets in a fight with a Roomba, Panda's life gets turned upside down when a mouse invades his room and Grizz gets stuck in a tree. You know, everyday stuff for a bear.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Primal
added.description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: The Pony
added.description: Gumball and Darwin race home to spend quality time with Anais, but every likely obstacle gets in way... and some unlikely ones too!

added.title: The Phone
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin get their first cell phone, they foolishly give out their number to super-intense Ocho.

added.title: The Photo
added.description: It's school picture day and Gumball has until 3pm to take one good photo - or have his legacy ruined forever.

added.title: The Plan
added.description: The Watterson kids come up with a fool-proof plan to save their mom, but is it Gumball-proof?

added.title: The Refund
added.description: Gumball and Darwin unsuccessfully attempt to get a refund for their computer game.

added.title: Mayhem in Mascot
added.description: After their attempt to get a photo with every storefront mascot is foiled, Ben and Gwen sneak out at night to get their photo with the wooden bear totem known as "Yawk", only to find he and the other mascots have come to life!

added.title: High Stress Express
added.description: During a live feed of the new transcontinental bullet train, La Grange enters the picture to outrace the train, but Ben joins in on the fun and will stop at nothing to come out on top!

added.title: Fear the Fogg
added.description: As Max attempts to get Ben and Gwen to the Four Corners Monument before sunset, an ominous fog bank engulfs the roadway and forces Max to drive at a snails pace, but once The Fogg comes to life and attacks the Rust Bucket, Team Tennyson must work together if they are to navigate to safety.

added.title: King Koil
added.description: Ben and Gwen spend the day volunteering at Repto Ranch and come face to face with King Koil, but need to quickly overcome their fear of snakes if they are to rescue the released critters and defeat the slithery baddie.

added.title: Past Aliens Present
added.description: After Ben stumbles upon a video of Cannonbolt ripping up a computer lab on the internet, Team Tennyson must race to State U to find the imposter; but once Ben discovers it is a steam-punk version of his alien that is terrorizing the campus, Ben must take down the man behind the machine, Steam Smythe!

added.title: Ghosts Schmosts
added.description: Seth leads a group of kids into a haunted mine in an effort to prove that everything has a scientific explanation and that there's no reason to be afraid ghosts. But things get spooky when they encounter a ghost that Seth doesn't have a scientific explanation for. Seth has to learn to give into his fear in order to and solve the mystery of the mine ghost.

added.title: Hide and Pam
added.description: Hide and Pam: Pam learns to play hide and seek a little too well./Chair Factory: Seth improves productivity at the Fancytown chair factory./Turtle: Seth brings a shy turtle for show and tell./Rainy Day: Cool James teaches the other kids how to have fun making music on a rainy day./Best Friends Club: Lil' Lemon and Nevin hold the first meeting of the Best Friends Club.

added.title: Reunion
added.description: When Daffy doesn't want to go to his class reunion because he feels he peaked in high school,  Bugs tries to help him make something of himself before the big night.

added.title: Casa de Calma
added.description: Instead of  relaxing during a spa vacation, Bugs and Daffy spend most of their time fighting over a Hollywood starlet.

added.title: Devil Dog
added.description: When the Tasmanian Devil escapes from the local zoo and shows up on Bugs and Daffy's doorstep, Daffy is terrified. Bugs, however, thinks he's just a lost dog and adopts him.

added.title: The Foghorn Leghorn Story
added.description: Foghorn Leghorn casts Daffy as himself in a movie about his life.  Meanwhile, Bugs and Yosemite Sam find a potentially valuable vase buried in the back yard.

added.title: Eligible Bachelors
added.description: While Lola sweeps Bugs to Paris in an effort to fall in love, Daffy sweeps Granny's attic and discovers that she was once a spy in WWII!

added.title: The News Never Sleeps!
added.description: Lil' Nelson takes a job as a paperboy, which is more difficult than it sounds in a city overrun by scorching Pyro Vipers and an evil Serpentine sorceress.

added.title: Ninja vs. Lava
added.description: The ninja find themselves trapped in a pyramid and must escape encroaching lava to warn NINJAGO City of a new Serpentine invasion.

added.title: Snaketastrophy
added.description: The Serpentine attack on NINJAGO City is seen from an unexpected perspective - entirely in the style of a live newscast delivered by Gayle Gossip and her cameraman.

added.title: Powerless
added.description: The ninja rush to the NINJAGO Museum of History to recover a dangerous scroll before it falls into the hands of the Serpentine Sorceress Aspheera.

added.title: Ancient History
added.description: While Aspheera pursues revenge on the "Treacherous Deceiver" who betrayed her, the ninja make a startling discovery.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: #IllusionsOfGrandeur
added.description: Ready to emerge from her father's shadow, Zee Zatara secretly seeks fame and acclaim performing for her own audience at the pier. But when her act is dismissed as fakery, she loses her cool and accidentally unleashes mischievous gremlins who run wild all over the pier.

added.title: #BeastsInShow
added.description: When Babs and Kara spar over whose dog is better, they decide to settle it at the Metropolis Dog Show, where Ace the Bat-Hound and Krypto the Superdog suddenly find themselves called upon to save the day… in more ways than one.

added.title: #GothamCon
added.description: A fun day for Barbara Gordon and her bestie Harleen Quinzel (at Gotham City's annual geekfest, the Annual Convention of Gotham City Enthusiats!) is turned on its head when, out of nowhere, the villainous Harley Quinn shows up to wreak havoc! Lucky for everyone, Batgirl just happens to be in the area...

added.title: Barbastella
added.description: While flying with his new invention, Panthro hits it off with a new friend, Barbastella, the Queen of the Bats! Now Panthro needs help getting ready for his big date with her, because it turns out Panthro is terrified of bats! Lion-O and Cheetara are happy to help but, wow, that is a lot to unpack.

added.title: Adopt a Jackal
added.description: After a battle with the Mutants, Jackalman gets confused and accidentally returns to the Cats' Lair with the Thundercats, he is the dumbest mutant. Jackalman pretends to be a Thundercat so his enemies won't catch him and the Thundercats pretend to play along because they feel bad for him!

added.title: Summer Fun Day!
added.description: The Thundercats are exhausted from fighting bad guys all the time so Lion-O suggests they spend a relaxing summer fun day at the beach, with no fighting! Unfortunately the beach is home to the Crabmen, giant, clawed humanoids that fight anyone who steps on their sand! Looks like summer fun day might involve some fighting!

added.title: Safari Joe
added.description: While minding her own business, Cheetara is caught in a trap set by Safari Joe, the famously annoying hunter! After escaping, she rallies the other ThunderCats to help her stop Joe once and for all, by turning the tables and capturing him!

added.title: Ratar-O
added.description: The ThunderCats have gotten so good at defeating the Mutants of Plun-Darr that it's basically become routine. That all changes with the arrival of the Mutants' old leader: Ratar-O, wielder of the Sword of Plun-Darr! Uh-oh!

added.title: Nightmare Hospital
added.description: Steven and Connie sneak into a hospital to recover Rose's Sword.

added.title: Sadie's Song
added.description: Steven helps Sadie put together an act for Beachapalooza.

added.title: Catch and Release
added.description: We finally see inside Steven's bathroom.

added.title: When It Rains
added.description: Steven helps a friend who's afraid of thunderstorms.

added.title: Back to the Barn
added.description: Steven and the Gems head back to the family barn to build some robots.

added.title: Head Chef
added.description: Mao Mao faces off with Badgerclops in a competition to determine whether cooking (and being a hero) is an art or a science.

added.title: Sugar Berry Fever
added.description: Mao Mao tries to hide his love of cobbler.

added.title: Web Weirdos
added.description: When Finn gets trapped in a giant spider web, he ends up playing marriage counselor to a couple of grumpy arachnids.

added.title: Return to the Nightosphere
added.description: Marceline's dad banishes Finn and Jake to the Nightosphere, and it stinks. Literally.

added.title: Sons of Mars
added.description: A case of Martian mistaken identity comes to Ooo when Magic Man turns Jake into a copy of himself.

added.title: The Hard Easy
added.description: A delicate race of frog people employ Finn and Jake to help them deal with Prince Huge, an evil lizard creature who's ravaging the moss swamp.

added.title: The Lich
added.description: A visit from the Lich King shines some light on some of Ooo's secrets.

added.title: Too Cool
added.description: Puppycorn needs a lesson in how to be cool. The gang is more than happy to teach him, until his coolness unexpectedly freezes the whole kingdom.

added.title: Guardian of the Unikingdom
added.description: Hawkodile insists the Unikingdom is more dangerous than it looks and sets out to prove it by taking his friends on bodyguard patrol.

added.title: Cast Aside the Truth
added.description: Hawkodile breaks his arm in a careless spill and lies to his friends about the accident to keep from looking bad.

added.title: Unikitty and the Ice Pop Factory
added.description: An eccentric figure announces a contest to tour her marvelous ice pop factory, sending the gang on a frantic quest to find the winning popsicle stick.

added.title: Sunken Treasure
added.description: A relaxing beach day becomes an underwater adventure when Unikitty and her friends find a message in a bottle.

added.title: New Direction
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the best directors in the business help a kid in need of acting lessons become a star.

added.title: Robo-UG
added.description: Uncle Grandpa builds a robot version of himself to help with his duties.

added.title: Licacion
added.description: Robin les presenta a los demás Titanes una aplicación para generar dinero, pero pronto conocen los peligros de una economía compartida.

added.title: Dia del Trabajo
added.description: Llegó el Día del Trabajo, y Robin les enseña a los demás Titanes la importancia del trabajo.

added.title: Titanes Clasicos
added.description: Para demostrar su punto de vista sobre los dibujos animados clásicos de superhéroes, iControl Freak envía a los Titanes a una versión antigua de Jóvenes Titanes en Acción!

added.title: Unos y Ceros
added.description: Los Titanes construyen un robot con inteligencia artificial para que elabore una pizza que nunca antes fue hecha.

added.title: Dia de los Trabajos
added.description: Robin obliga a los demás Titanes a olvidar sus sueños y a conseguir trabajos normales y aburridos.

added.title: In the House
added.description: Rigby eggs the wrong house and gets cursed by a wizard.

added.title: The Lady and the Queen/The AB's Silver Screen Debut
added.description: The Lady and the Queen: China Riot finds a new Bakugan: Barbetra. But this buzzy new Bakugan is a bit timid on the battleground. Riot takes her on as her new project to turn her into the battle queen she knows she can be./The AB's Silver Screen Debut: Lord Brakken and Duran have teamed up and are now the Bakugan film business. They look to the Awesome Brawlers for their expertise in both Bakugan culture and film making to get their movie made!

added.title: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!/Magnus
added.description: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing./Magnus: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League/The Ancient Elder
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League: Benton Dusk is in the process of renovating a state of the art Bakugan Brawling stadium. When it comes to brawling, who better to test out the new arena than the Awesome Brawlers!/The Ancient Elder: Dan finds a new baku-bud in Gillitar. Well "bud" may be too strong a word, Dan and gang quickly learn that Gillator has a few "quirks" that keep him from fitting in with the rest of the Awesome Brawler's Bakugan.

added.title: Bakugan Wynton/The Boy from Brazil
added.description: Bakugan Wynton: Wynton has a new device that tracks down Bakugan! Right out of the gate the device works and, Wynton meets: Batrix. Like his name, Batrix is a little batty, and these two are certainly in for a "batty" first adventure./The Boy from Brazil: The Awesome Brawlers are off to a soccer match! In the process of doing so Shun discovers a new Bakugan friend, the boisterous Ramparian, and a new foe in Brazilian soccer star: Pepe.

added.title: Relaxation Land
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's relaxing weekend getaway quickly becomes a spooky nightmare for Pizza Steve.

added.title: House Rules
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are sick of Benson's house rules and want to live without them.

added.title: Haunted House/Two of a Kind
added.description: Haunted House: Rumor has it that there's a haunted building in Los Volmos, and the Awesome Brawlers are on the case! Who doesn't like a good ghost hunt, plus capturing a ghost on camera should make Awesome Brawlers' next video a huge success!/Two of a Kind: Veronica Venegas is doing a special report on the Awesome brawlers own: Lightening! The special report takes a back seat when Lightening is challenged to a brawl. Lightening uses this brawl the perfect opportunity to rollout his new Bakugan partner: Tretorous.

added.title: Muscle Mentor
added.description: Rigby gets mentored by Muscle Man.

added.title: Out of Commission
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have one last day with the cart before they have to get rid of it.

added.title: Prankless
added.description: The guys want to win a prank war with a rival park.

added.title: Big Tick
added.description: A giant alien tick that sucks planets dry, lands on Earth with the sole purpose of destroying the planet and only a new alien hero can stop it.

added.title: Desastre en Mascota
added.description: Frustrado su intento de conseguir una foto con cada mascota de vidriera, Ben y Gwen se escabullen de noche para tomarse su foto con el tótem del oso de madera... iy descubren que él y las demás mascotas cobraron vida!

added.title: Grudge Match
added.description: Ben and Kevin 11 are beamed up to a space ship where must learn to battle together in order to bring down a vicious alien fight promoter.

added.title: Older
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa mistakenly transforms a young boy into a three-hundred-year-old man, he must manage to turn the kid back to normal before anyone gets hurt.

added.title: Expreso De Gran Estres
added.description: Durante una transmisión en vivo del nuevo tren bala transcontinental, La Grange se cuela para ganarle al tren. Pero Ben se suma a la diversión, iy no se detendrá ante nada para salir victorioso!

added.title: Teman a la Niebla
added.description: Mientras Max intenta llevar a Ben y Gwen al Monumento de las Cuatro Esquinas antes del atardecer, un banco de niebla siniestra envuelve la carretera y obliga a Max a conducir a la velocidad de un caracol. Pero una vez que Fogg cobra vida y ataca el Rust Bucket, el equipo Tennyson debe trabajar unido si se quieren llegar sanos y salvos.

added.title: Rey Koil
added.description: Ben y Gwen pasan el día como voluntarios en Repto Ranch y se enfrentan cara a cara con el Rey Koil. Pero necesitan superar rápidamente su miedo a las serpientes si quieren rescatar a las criaturas liberadas y derrotar al serpenteante villano.

added.title: Mustache Tree
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa runs out of mustaches, he travels to the mustache tree to stock up. But upon arrival, it seems a new clan of elves have become very territorial over the tree. Now, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must fight in order to obtain a new 'stache.

added.title: Alienigenas del Pasado, Presente
added.description: Cuando Ben encuentra un video en Internet en el que Cannonbolt destruye un laboratorio informático, el equipo Tennyson debe correr a State U para encontrar al impostor. Pero una vez que Ben descubra que una versión a vapor de su alienígena es la que está aterrorizando al campus, deberá derribar al hombre que está detrás de la máquina: iVapor Smythe!

added.title: Fun Dungeon Face Off
added.description: Clarence's Mom treats Clarence, Jeff and Sumo to an afternoon at Rough Riders Chicken, a fast food restaurant with a play emporium. When Clarence and Sumo steal Jeff's fries, Jeff is forced to confront his germ phobias head-on in the restaurant's seemingly unsanitary play area.

added.title: Capullos de Rosa
added.description: Steven recibe una visita sorpresa de algunos viejos amigos y una introducción aún más sorprendente a algunos nuevos.

added.title: Voleibol
added.description: Steven está decidido a ayudar a la Perla original de Diamante Rosa para sanar la cicatriz en su rostro.

added.title: Las Noticias Nunca Duermen
added.description: Lil 'Nelson toma un trabajo como repartidor de periódicos, lo cual es más difícil de lo que parece en una ciudad invadida por Pyro Vipers y una malvada hechicera serpentina.

added.title: Osos Cotidianos
added.description: Hoy es un día normal para los Osos. Eso significa que Ice se pelea con Roomba, que la vida de Panda queda patas arriba cuando un ratón invade su habitación y que Pardo queda varado en un árbol. Ya saben, las típicas cosas que les suceden a los osos.

added.title: Ninja Contra Lava
added.description: Los ninja se encuentran atrapados en una pirámide y deben escapar de la lava invasora para advertir a la ciudad de NINJAGO de una nueva invasión serpentina.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: A Pardo le gustan los burritos. Mucho. Tanto que cuando un restaurant elabora un Burrito tamaño oso, Pardo se obliga a comer semejante obra de arte majestuosa. Lleva el burrito consigo a todas partes y lo convierte en una parte nueva y cada vez más olorosa de su vida.

added.title: Naturaleza
added.description: ¿Acaso los Osos perdieron sus instintos de supervivencia en el mundo moderno? Pardo quiere saberlo, así que lleva a los Osos para que se pierdan intencionalmente en las profundidades del bosque.

added.title: Serpientastrofe
added.description: El ataque de Serpentine en NINJAGO City se ve desde una perspectiva inesperada, completamente al estilo de un noticiero en vivo entregado por Gayle Gossip y su camarógrafo.

added.title: Chaqueta De Mezclilla
added.description: Los Osos encuentran una chaqueta de jean deslumbrante en un contenedor de basura. Es una de las cosas más fabulosas que jamás hayan visto, y parece convertir a aquel que la use en una persona extremadamente afortunada. Pero cuando los Osos discuten para ver quién queda a cargo de la chaqueta, empiezan a pensar que su bendición de denim se convirtió en una maldición.

added.title: Impotente
added.description: El ninja corre al Museo de Historia de NINJAGO para recuperar un pergamino peligroso antes de que caiga en manos de la Hechicera Serpentina Aspheera.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: Cuando, luego de un accidente reciente, Nom Nom aparece en la entrada de la casa de los Osos, desaliñado y destronado de su puesto como la estrella más tierna de Internet de la historia, consigue la ayuda de los Osos para tratar de recuperar su título.

added.title: Historia Antigua
added.description: Mientras Aspheera busca vengarse del "Engañador Traicionero" que la traicionó, el ninja hace un sorprendente descubrimiento.

added.title: Dollar Hunt
added.description: Clarence hosts a fun "dollar hunt" game to meet new friends. But things go awry when Clarence accidentally buries the money his Mom gave him to buy refreshments for her book club meeting.

added.title: Secrets
added.description: Grandpa Max's mysterious past comes to light when Vilgax shows up on earth in search of the Omnitrix. And the family must work together to defeat him.

added.title: Dream Boat
added.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

added.title: #IlusionesDeGrandeza
added.description: Lista para salir de la sombra de su padre, Zatara busca la fama y el reconocimiento con una presentación para su propia audiencia en el muelle. Pero cuando su acto es tildado de fraude, ella pierde el control y accidentalmente libera terribles seres que causan estragos en el muelle.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #LaConvencionDeGotham
added.description: Un divertido día para Barbara Gordon y su mejor amiga Harley Quinzel en la Convención Anual de Gotham City, es puesto cabeza abajo cuando, de la nada, ila malvada Harley Quinn aparece para sembrar el caos! Por suerte para todos, Batgirl se encuentra casualmente en el área...
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Bowling for Ballers
added.description: Axel and the team must intervene when Zoe's not-so-friendly bowling competition with Cleo LeBall gets interrupted by Madcap, Porcupunk, and their new cohort, the mischievously magnetic Dynamo.

added.title: Countdown
added.description: Axel has to clean up the living room in time for his uncle's dinner party, but trying to do too much at once leaves him stuck as a toy with Orangutank on the loose and less than an hour until the guests arrive.

added.title: Joke's on You, Bro!
added.description: Axel and the team turn Galileo's camouflaging pranks around on him, convincing the gullible gecko that he's permanently invisible - to disastrous results!

added.title: Out of My Head
added.description: Axel must help Sarge and Bobbie learn to walk in each other's shoes - literally - after Luka unwittingly switches the toys' heads!

added.title: Evil's Encore
added.description: Dr. Animo reminisces about when he once took control of the Plumber's HQ in Mount Rushmore. (Flashback episode.)

added.title: Freeze!
added.description: Axel and his team find themselves in a tough position after Ice Crusher makes it too cold for them to fight back at full speed.

added.title: Goose Chase
added.description: While at the park, Clarence happily feeds some birds his sandwich, imagining himself as their king. He has a great time until one persistent goose will not leave him alone!

added.title: Return to Forever
added.description: The Forever Knights threaten to use a sinister weapon to erase all alien DNA on Earth unless Ben and Rook can stop them.

added.title: Dust Buddies
added.description: As punishment for making a huge mess in their house, Belson's mom makes Belson clean up, offering their usual maid service to Mary and Clarence. Embarrassed of their messy house, Mary and Clarence hurry to clean up before the maid arrives.

added.title: OTTO Motive
added.description: Kevin and Rook run into an old enemy from the Null Void while attending an intergalactic auto show. (Re-introducing classic Ben alien, Upgrade.)

added.title: A Fistful of Brains
added.description: Grandpa Max and Rook are looking all over the galaxy for Ben, who is trapped on Khyber's hidden personal hunting preserve.

added.title: Mystery, Incorporeal
added.description: An old enemy emerges while Ben and Rook visit Kevin and Gwen at college.

added.title: Bolos para Campeonas
added.description: Axel y el equipo deben intervenir cuando la competencia de bolos no tan amigable de Zoe con Cleo LeBall es interrumpida por Madcap, Porcupunk y su nueva cohorte, el travieso Dynamo magnético.

added.title: Fiebre de la Baya de Azúcar
added.description: Mao Mao intenta ocultar su amor por el pastel de fruta.

added.title: #ElShowDeLasBestias
added.description: Cuando Babs y Kara discuten sobre cual de sus perros es mejor, deciden resolver la situación en el concurso anual de perros de Metrópolis, donde Ace, el Bati-sabueso y Krypto, el Superperro, deberán salvar el día.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Jefe de Cocina
added.description: Mao Mao se enfrenta a Colosal en una competencia para determinar si cocinar (y ser un héroe) es un arte o una ciencia.

added.title: Fuera de Mi Cabeza
added.description: iAxel debe ayudar a Sarge y Bobbie a aprender a caminar en los zapatos del otro, literalmente, después de que Luka involuntariamente cambia las cabezas de los juguetes!

added.title: Cuenta Regresiva
added.description: Axel tiene que limpiar la sala de estar a tiempo para la cena de su tío, pero tratar de hacer demasiado de una vez lo deja atrapado como un juguete con Orangutank suelto y menos de una hora hasta que lleguen los invitados.

added.title: Congelados
added.description: Axel y su equipo se encuentran en una posición difícil después de que Ice Crusher hace demasiado frío para que puedan defenderse a toda velocidad.

added.title: Ahora Te Toca a Ti, Amigo
added.description: Axel y el equipo giran las bromas de camuflaje de Galileo sobre él, convenciendo al crédulo gecko de que es permanentemente invisible, ipara obtener resultados desastrosos!

removed.title: Saving Private Masko
removed.description: Masko takes Axel's call for more discipline too seriously and loses sight of his own identity in the process, becoming a no-nonsense soldier set on toeing the line - and ill-equipped for a lucha libre with Madcap!

removed.title: Potencial Desperdiciado
removed.description: A raíz de la victoria de la temporada anterior, los ninjas se han ablandado y el Maestro Wu debe recordarles quiénes son realmente.

removed.title: Jugo arcoiris
removed.description: Después de desafiarse unos a otros a tomar el Latte de Pegaso de Chef, Izzy y Jude están llenos de energía y Duncan y Courtney hacen un viaje por carretera para tratar de reemplazar la bebida antes de que Chef descubra que desapareció.

removed.title: #MisgivingTree
removed.description: Jessica Cruz and Pam Isley bond over protecting an ancient tree from being cut down. Neither of them realizes who the other's alter ego is, or the lengths to which they'll go to protect what's important.

removed.title: The Twins Bug Seth
removed.description: Seth neglects his baby-sitting duties to do his own thing and winds up losing the twins to an army of ants! On his undercover mission to get back the Twins, Seth learns to appreciate his siblings even if they're a little annoying at times.

removed.title: A Rocky Start
removed.description: The ninja have found their quest! Now they just have to get there, which involves a road trip through the Desert of Doom, a region supposedly inhabited by a giant scarab beetle.

removed.title: Cluckwork Orange
removed.description: After befriending a chicken with a bad attitude at a petting zoo, Jude is followed back to school by the chicken. He defends the bad bird's behavior until he can defend it no longer.
